# Implementation Workflow

## Standard Cycle

### 1. Plan
- Read affected layers: `handlers` → `services` → `repositories` → `models`
- Check `go-layering.mdc` import boundaries
- Note IAM implications (auth, sessions, OIDC)

### 2. Implement
- Match existing patterns in the same package
- Wire new deps in `cmd/server/main.go` (FX) and routes in `router.go`
- Handle errors with `AppError` where the file already does

### 3. Test
- Add/update colocated `*_test.go`
- Run narrow target first: `go test ./internal/handlers` (or services/repos)
- Full suite: `make tests`

### 4. HTTP / OpenAPI
- `/api/v1` changes: swag annotations + `make swagger-load`
- Root OIDC changes: update matching [docs/features/](../../docs/features/) and [docs/testing/](../../docs/testing/) docs (not in swag spec)
- CSRF: update `internal/middlewares/csrf.go` if new paths need skip rules

### 5. Migrations
- If schema changed: new SQL in `cmd/migrations/sql/` + `make migrate-hash`

### 6. Review & Integrate
- Self-review diff; `make lint`
- Conventional commit; PR with test plan

## Bug Fix Workflow
1. Reproduce (test or curl flow doc)
2. Root cause — don't patch symptoms
3. Minimal fix at correct layer
4. Regression test
5. `make tests`

## Local Dev Commands
```bash
make container-up   # Postgres, Redis, etc.
make migrate-up     # Apply Atlas migrations
make up             # Run server (cmd/server)
make bootstrap      # container-up + migrate-up + up
```
